    {
      "id": 45,
      "type": "Note",
      "pos": [
        -1603.0876141915041,
        90.55597017873693
      ],
      "size": [
        386.16473214043697,
        838.2864444723772
      ],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 14,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "title": "model",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "I recommend DISTILLED model particularly gguf versions of ltxvideo 2.3\n\n(https://huggingface.co/unsloth/LTX-2.3-GGUF/tree/main/distilled)\n\nYou can run it in around 8-10 steps with the single stage workflow. (this is a modified workflow from Kijai. it doesn't do second stage so no upscaling.)\n\nFor clip(s) : Use the fp8 one\n\n(https://huggingface.co/Comfy-Org/ltx-2/blob/main/split_files/text_encoders/gemma_3_12B_it_fp8_scaled.safetensors) \n\n-tried gguf's , it doesn't make much difference with this clip, it is very demanding , especially if you are using clip realtime on the workflow aka not caching prompts beforehand. So stick with fp8 at least it is as best as you can get)\n\nand this for the second clip model ;\n\n(https://huggingface.co/Kijai/LTX2.3_comfy/blob/main/text_encoders/ltx-2.3_text_projection_bf16.safetensors)\n\nvideo vae & audio vae : \n\n(https://huggingface.co/Kijai/LTX2.3_comfy/tree/main/vae)\n\nspatio temporal tiled vae decode :\nit is from ltxvideo themselves, available with their nodes. key point is how many spatial tiles you use, if you enter 2 it would 2x2 etc. VRAM usage would be lower but it would that a bit longer but not as bad as using normal vae encode and getting OOM in the end of a long run ...\n\n* enabled use_fp16 on this node, no problems on the end results.\n\n"
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    }
